<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ideefc1f97-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s1765e"><num value="1765e">§ 1765e.</num><heading> Location of offices</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">United States Agricultural Trade Offices shall be centrally located in the cities of assignment to facilitate foreign trade meetings and foreign trade reliance on such offices for assistance in marketing activities.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ideefc1f98-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-28/ch1041">Aug. 28, 1954, ch. 1041</ref>, title VI, § 605E, as added <ref href="/us/pl/95/501/tIV/s401/1">Pub. L. 95–501, title IV, § 401(1)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-21">Oct. 21, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1690">92 Stat. 1690</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
